### TITLE ###
DefaultBeforeCaseSuggestsReorder
### DESCRIPTION ###
`default:` appearing before any `case:` arm in a switch.
The grammar requires `default` last; today the parser bails
with a misleading "Invalid function syntax" error on the
enclosing function header. The new heuristic recognises the
misordered shape and emits a single targeted suggestion at
the file-level ERROR, suppressing the cascade RAD10001s
from the inner ERRORs.
### INPUT ###
fn f(x: str):
    switch x:
        default:
            print("d")
        case "a":
            print("a")
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  (none)

# Symbol types
  (none)

# Diagnostics
  [error] RAD10001 @ 1:1 - 'default' arm must appear last in a switch
    help: Move the 'default' arm so it appears after all 'case' arms
### TITLE ###
DefaultAfterCaseStillValid
### DESCRIPTION ###
Regression lock: the canonical default-after-case shape
must still parse cleanly. The new heuristic only fires on
the misordered form.
### INPUT ###
fn f(x: str):
    switch x:
        case "a":
            print("a")
        default:
            print("d")
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  x @ 2:12 -> str
  print @ 4:13 -> dynamic
  print @ 6:13 -> dynamic

# Symbol types
  f (fn): fn(str) -> void
  x (param): str

# Diagnostics
  (none)
